net.sf.mmm.music.datatype.api

Enum ChordExtension

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ChordExtension>
      • net.sf.mmm.music.datatype.api.ChordExtension
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ChordExtension>

    public enum ChordExtension
extends Enum<ChordExtension>
    A ChordExtension extends a Chord with additional intervals or may also replace existing intervals. These are typically numbers, specific strings or symbols added to a Chord-name.
    Author:
    hohwille

      Adds a ChromaticInterval.MAJOR_SECOND to the Chord.

      Adds a ChromaticInterval.PERFECT_FOURTH to the Chord.
      ADD_9
      Adds a ChromaticInterval.MAJOR_NINTH to the Chord.
      AUG
      Augmented triad is an extension that removes the third and fifth of the Chord and replaces them with a ChromaticInterval.MAJOR_THIRD and a ChromaticInterval.MAJOR_SIXT.
      DIM
      Diminished extension that removes the third and fifth of the Chord and replaces them with a ChromaticInterval.MINOR_THIRD and a ChromaticInterval.DIMINISHED_FIFTH.
      MAJ_7
      Adds a ChromaticInterval.MAJOR_SEVENTH to the Chord.
      MAJ_9

      NO_3
      Removes the third of the Chord.
      NO_5
      Removes the fifth of the Chord.
      SUS_2
      Replaces the third (suspended) of the Chord with a ChromaticInterval.MAJOR_SECOND.
      SUS_4
      Replaces the third (suspended) of the Chord with a ChromaticInterval.PERFECT_FOURTH.

      • getExtensionPrefix

        public static String getExtensionPrefix(String string)
        This method gets the longest string representation of the ChordExtension that is a prefix of the given string ignoring the case. E.g. for "add9sus4" it would return "add9" and for "49" it would return "4".
        Parameters:
        string - is a String supposed to start with the title of the ChordExtension which is the name, alternative name or symbol representation in any case.
        Returns:
        the requested ChordExtension or null if no such ChordExtension exists.
        See Also:
        fromString(String)
